    "(3.3) JHEP05(2024)196This expression is valid for both light and heavy fields (i.e.",
    "for both purely real and purely imaginary ν), and we have used [W a,b (z)] * = W a *,b * (z *) and the symmetry property W a,-b (z) = W a,b (z).",
    "The power spectrum of each helicity mode is different due to the c h,S and κ dependence.",
    "Parity violation is then encoded in the asymmetry between opposite helicities.",
    "It can be further shown that the IR expansion of the power spectrum contains enhanced oscillations in η 0 due to particle production assisted by the chemical potential, which leads to lifted cosmological collider signals (see, e.g."
